attributes.Long form description: The student is not sure where to start, but the teacher quickly tells him to start with the legs of the chair. The student then places them on top of each other to start screwing them together. The teacher helps him by telling him with which tools he can do the job better. The student then turns the legs upside down to make it easier to put the seat of the chair in place.  Then he places and screws the four screws and saddle washers in place. Finally, the student gives a final screw to the hex nut in the center of the chair to make sure it is in place.
